// `clone_vec_u8` has the single ensures `out@ == v@`, and the determinism
// predicate is `det_clone_vec_u8_equal(r1, r2) := (r1 == r2)`. So the
// synthetic obligation reduces to:
//   (r1@ == v@) && (r2@ == v@)  ==>  r1 == r2.
// z3 returns `unknown` because the two ensures-conjuncts (one per run)
// share no top-level trigger: the Seq-equality `r1@ == v@` and `r2@ == v@`
// never get lined up under the same instantiation. Re-asserting them under
// a case-split, chaining through Seq transitivity, and finishing with
// extensional equality (`=~=`) pins the trigger and lets the Vec-equality
// axiom (Vec<u8> == iff its Seq<u8> view ==) fire.
assert((r1@ == v@ && r2@ == v@) ==> det_clone_vec_u8_equal(r1, r2)) by {
    if r1@ == v@ && r2@ == v@ {
        // Re-state the two ensures so both get instantiated in this context.
        assert(r1@ == v@);
        assert(r2@ == v@);
        // Transitivity at the Seq<u8> level.
        assert(r1@ == r2@);
        // Seq extensional equality — re-seats the trigger so the
        // Vec<u8> equality axiom can lift Seq-view equality to Vec ==.
        assert(r1@ =~= r2@);
    }
}
